=============================================================================
TELE-REMOTE COMMUNICATION ARCHITECTURE (RESUME)
=============================================================================

This document summarizes the current data flow and messaging paradigms used
inside the Tele-Remote ecosystem.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. HIGH-LEVEL DATA FLOW (ASCII)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

         [ TELEGRAM APP ]           [ TELE-REMOTE SERVER (GO) ]        [ CLIENT COMPONENTS ]
                |                             |                             |
                | (1) Command (Inline Button) |                             |
                |---------------------------->|                             |
                |                             | (2) PublishCommand (ctx)    |
                |                             |---------------------------->|
                |                             |                             |
                |                             | (3) Execute Logic (Bot)     |
                |                             |<----------------------------|
                |                             |                             |
                | (4) Telemetry / Log Update  |                             |
                |<----------------------------|                             |
                |                             | (5) Stream / Post Data      |
                |                             |<----------------------------|
                |                             |                             |

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. COMPONENT REGISTRATION (MENU-ON-THE-FLY)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

When a client (Trading Bot, Ingestor, etc.) connects, it performs a
"Registration" handshake. It sends a structured JSON payload containing its:
- Component Name
- Registration Metadata
- Menu JSON (recursive tree of buttons, commands, and sub-menus)

Tele-Remote parses this on-the-fly, dynamically builds a Telegram keyboard,
and maps every button click back to the specific "Publisher" associated
with that connection.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. TRANSPORT MULTIPLEXING
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Tele-Remote is protocol-agnostic. It supports three primary transport methods:

a) gRPC:        High-performance, typed bidirectional streams.
b) NATS:        Distributed pub/sub via NATS Jetstream topics.
c) SafeSocket:  Low-overhead TCP/Unix socket communication.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. SHARED DEPENDENCIES
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

- flexible-logger:    Unified logging format across all Bastien's services.
- message-serializers: Shared Go library for GOB/JSON binary marshaling.
- distributed-config: Remote configuration for cloud-native deployment.

=============================================================================
EOF
